title: Two girls in custody suspected of killing 12-year-old child
description: Two children are suspected of killing a 12-year-old girl in Germany in a case which has shocked the country.

title: Member of boat smuggling gang found hiding in attic by German police dog
description: A suspected member of an international trafficking ring which allegedly smuggled thousands of people across the English Channel has been arrested in Germany.

title: Eva Green 'contemplated faking a broken arm' to avoid appearing in film, High Court told
description: Hollywood actress Eva Green "contemplated faking a broken arm" to avoid appearing in a later-abandoned sci-fi movie, the High Court has been told.

title: 'We need more of everything': Ukrainian soldiers demand extra Western weapons to defend Bakhmut
description: There's an eerie sense of foreboding in the villages, towns, and cities of eastern Ukraine - especially those within firing distance of Russian artillery, and the fighting in the nearby city of Bakhmut.

title: Russian jets dumped fuel in front of US drone before crash which could lead to 'unintended escalation'
description: A Russian aircraft has collided with a US unmanned aircraft in international airspace over the Black Sea, causing it to crash.

title: Man suing restaurant chain after claiming boneless wings are actually just chicken nuggets
description: In a decade where the world has faced a global pandemic, the threat of nuclear war, and a rise in the cost of living - a man in the US claims he has encountered another crisis to add to the mounting list of problems facing our species.

title: Former Pakistan PM Imran Khan 'prepared for arrest' as police clash with supporters
description: Imran Khan has said he is "mentally prepared for arrest" as police battle supporters outside his home in eastern Pakistan.

title: Facebook and Instagram owner Meta to lay off another 10,000 staff
description: Meta, the owner of Facebook and Instagram, is axing another 10,000 jobs to cut costs.

title: 'It makes me sick': 5,600 tons of rubbish transforms Paris into dump as binmen strike continues
description: Paris has been overwhelmed by more than 5,000 tons of waste as binmen remained on strike for a ninth consecutive day.

title: World Cup expansion to have more matches than originally planned
description: FIFA is set to approve an expansion of the men's World Cup today with 40 more matches from the 2026 tournament in North America, Sky News understands.

title: Where TikTok is restricted around the world as the UK considers taking action
description: TikTok could find itself in the crosshairs of UK authorities as they consider whether the video-sharing app should be banned.

title: What is the AUKUS submarines pact between the UK, US and Australia?
description: The AUKUS pact between the UK, US and Australia to create a new fleet of nuclear-powered submarines to patrol the Pacific Ocean is not popular everywhere, including with a key NATO ally.

title: Poor sleep before a vaccine could make it less effective - especially for men, study finds
description: Sleeping less than six hours in the days around a vaccination could reduce the body's immune response, leaving you more vulnerable to infection, a new study has found.

title: China accuses UK, US and Australia of 'going further down dangerous road' with submarine pact
description: China has hit out at the US, UK and Australia over their pact to create new nuclear-powered submarines, saying they have "gone further down a dangerous road".

title: Andrew Tate loses fresh appeal to be released from Romanian prison
description: Andrew Tate's appeal against a 30-day extension of his detention in Romania has been denied by a court, meaning the social media influencer will remain in prison.

title: Record-breaking cyclone that won't end kills dozens in southern Africa
description: A long-lasting cyclone that is refusing to dissipate has torn through Malawi and Mozambique killing at least 56 people and leaving many others injured or missing.

title: Joe Biden to visit Northern Ireland and the Republic of Ireland
description: Joe Biden will visit Northern Ireland following a formal invitation from Prime Minister Rishi Sunak.
